      "JSAs, work permits, and photos reviewed"
    ],
    "summary": "On 9 September 2020 at 0830 hours at Main Pass 42 L, an information technology specialist stepped into an open floor panel while installing a new cable in the Motor Control Center (MCC) Building, fracturing his left leg. The injury was caused by lack of awareness where the injured person lost track of his surroundings. A contributing factor was the failure to identify hazards prior to the job, as the task was considered routine and did not require a Job Safety Analysis.",
